{
  "texts": [
    "While laypeople consistently preferred the first sentence over the second in both pairs, ChatGPT tended to show the opposite preference.",
    "When shifting the attention from correlation to equivalence, we found that though ChatGPT and laypeople correlated in the ME task, their response patterns were noticeably distinct.",
    "Ratings from ChatGPT were more conservative than those from human participants in that grammatical sentences were rated lower by ChatGPT than by humans, while ungrammatical sentences were rated in the reversed trend.",
    "Aside from the ME task, differences between human participants and ChatGPT was minimal: In the LS task, the effect of participant type on rating scores was not statistically significant; as for the FC task, the difference between ChatGPT and humans, although existed, was almost negligible (89% vs 88%).",
    "We believe that the wider range of human rating scores in the ME task results from variations in the number of response options and differences in language processing styles between humans and ChatGPT."
  ]
}